WEBVTT

1
00:00:40.640 --> 00:00:43.480
This way.

2
00:01:00.120 --> 00:01:02.400
It's right here.

3
00:01:21.960 --> 00:01:24.680
Wait.

4
00:01:48.400 --> 00:01:50.616
It's all set. Don Minu.

5
00:01:50.640 --> 00:01:54.920
We're going to find
your grandson. don't worry.

6
00:02:20.560 --> 00:02:22.976
Where could your grandfather be?

7
00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:26.160
I told you I don't know.

8
00:02:27.120 --> 00:02:30.416
You know my grandfather
doesn't trust anyone.

9
00:02:30.440 --> 00:02:34.160
There aren't many places for him to hide.

10
00:02:50.480 --> 00:02:55.016
We can lay low here for a while.
I have a nice room for you.

11
00:02:55.040 --> 00:02:57.296
With a beautiful view.

12
00:02:57.320 --> 00:02:59.720
What should we eat tonight?

13
00:03:00.600 --> 00:03:02.856
You think we're stupid?

14
00:03:02.880 --> 00:03:06.760
You think the Curtigas
are a family of idiots?

15
00:03:08.200 --> 00:03:13.576
You all have bad blood.
you. your father. your grandfather...

16
00:03:13.600 --> 00:03:15.976
Wait!

17
00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:18.536
The ship didn't sink.

18
00:03:18.560 --> 00:03:22.080
The shipment's on its way. you hear me?

19
00:03:22.280 --> 00:03:23.576
Ah. really?

20
00:03:23.600 --> 00:03:27.560
My grandfather told me
the last time we saw each other.

21
00:03:38.040 --> 00:03:40.400
Get him.

22
00:06:39.600 --> 00:06:42.640
This way. come on.

23
00:07:00.440 --> 00:07:02.920
Wait. sweetheart.

24
00:07:06.200 --> 00:07:09.280
Duck down. go under.

25
00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:17.400
Move over a bit. good boy.

26
00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:30.776
Good morning.

27
00:07:30.800 --> 00:07:32.896
- Where's the lady?
- She's upstairs.

28
00:07:32.920 --> 00:07:34.216
- Give me a hand?
- Sure.

29
00:07:34.240 --> 00:07:37.440
Thank you. Come here.

30
00:07:39.320 --> 00:07:42.680
Straight ahead. into the courtyard.

31
00:07:45.560 --> 00:07:48.480
We're nearly there.

32
00:07:49.440 --> 00:07:51.936
- The lady?
- She's upstairs.

33
00:07:51.960 --> 00:07:54.360
Thank you.

34
00:07:56.840 --> 00:08:00.280
Domenico. hold on. we're nearly there.

35
00:08:04.640 --> 00:08:06.096
Good morning.

36
00:08:06.120 --> 00:08:08.376
- Where is she?
- In there.

37
00:08:08.400 --> 00:08:11.800
- Keep an eye on my kid. please.
- Come.

38
00:08:12.080 --> 00:08:15.240
- What's your name?
- Domenico.

39
00:08:22.280 --> 00:08:24.880
My respects.

40
00:08:38.160 --> 00:08:41.400
The Lord helps you.

41
00:08:41.720 --> 00:08:44.760
He helps for real.

42
00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:08.656
Here. Don Minu.

43
00:09:08.680 --> 00:09:11.456
Find anything out?

44
00:09:11.480 --> 00:09:14.536
There's no news from Stefano.

45
00:09:14.560 --> 00:09:18.040
But I got this from Lucia.

46
00:09:41.720 --> 00:09:46.160
Tell Bellantone to get Lucia.

47
00:10:15.760 --> 00:10:19.000
Mico. come here.

48
00:10:26.360 --> 00:10:28.776
Are you tired?

49
00:10:28.800 --> 00:10:30.376
A little bit?

50
00:10:30.400 --> 00:10:34.760
Everything's going to be fine.
don't worry. Okay?

51
00:10:45.040 --> 00:10:46.976
Lucia.

52
00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:49.136
Mico.

53
00:10:49.160 --> 00:10:51.136
Mico!

54
00:10:51.160 --> 00:10:52.616
Come on. come here.

55
00:10:52.640 --> 00:10:54.256
Come.

56
00:10:54.280 --> 00:10:57.096
All good? Let's go!

57
00:10:57.120 --> 00:10:59.376
Little guy!

58
00:10:59.400 --> 00:11:01.896
Hi. Shake my hand?

59
00:11:01.920 --> 00:11:03.936
Good boy!

60
00:11:03.960 --> 00:11:06.960
Let me hear you bark like a dog.

61
00:11:07.360 --> 00:11:09.216
Louder.

62
00:11:09.240 --> 00:11:11.696
Well done.

63
00:11:11.720 --> 00:11:14.640
Were you waiting long?

64
00:11:15.280 --> 00:11:17.560
No.

65
00:11:23.000 --> 00:11:25.320
Don Minu...

66
00:11:31.840 --> 00:11:35.760
Bellantone's sons
picked up Lucia and the boy.

67
00:11:42.240 --> 00:11:44.800
Good.

68
00:11:46.120 --> 00:11:48.960
That's good.

69
00:11:55.560 --> 00:11:58.736
- We've arrived.
- There's a car.

70
00:11:58.760 --> 00:12:01.560
There are no animals?

71
00:12:03.720 --> 00:12:07.000
- Will you get the suitcase?
- I'll get it.

72
00:12:10.160 --> 00:12:12.720
Come on. Mico.

73
00:12:14.520 --> 00:12:17.400
Be careful.

74
00:12:19.680 --> 00:12:21.216
Watch out.

75
00:12:21.240 --> 00:12:23.176
Get some rest. Lucia.

76
00:12:23.200 --> 00:12:25.576
Yes. thank you.

77
00:12:25.600 --> 00:12:28.920
Mico. come in.

78
00:12:30.560 --> 00:12:33.040
Let's go in.

79
00:12:46.760 --> 00:12:49.320
Domenico.

80
00:12:49.560 --> 00:12:51.920
Well?

81
00:12:55.760 --> 00:12:58.720
Relax. Lucia.

82
00:12:59.680 --> 00:13:04.280
If Stefano does as we say.
nothing will happen to you.

83
00:13:07.320 --> 00:13:10.480
You gonna open that door or not?

84
00:13:10.960 --> 00:13:13.296
- Stefano will get revenge.
- Sure...

85
00:13:13.320 --> 00:13:15.656
Move. get in there!

86
00:13:15.680 --> 00:13:18.856
Take it easy. Antonello!

87
00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:22.576
Calm down.
What are you worried about?

88
00:13:22.600 --> 00:13:25.496
Your father will understand. calm down.

89
00:13:25.520 --> 00:13:29.496
Betraying Don Minu is the smartest
move for the Bellantone family.

90
00:13:29.520 --> 00:13:32.616
- You've done the right thing.
- I know.

91
00:13:32.640 --> 00:13:35.056
Don Minu is old.
the world's spinning backwards.

92
00:13:35.080 --> 00:13:37.936
if we don't fix it. we'll disappear.

93
00:13:37.960 --> 00:13:41.200
Right? What do you say. Palmiro?

94
00:13:41.840 --> 00:13:44.560
It's like you say.

95
00:13:44.680 --> 00:13:46.920
Let's go.

96
00:14:03.080 --> 00:14:07.800
If you love your wife.
you better stop the fucking brokers.

97
00:14:17.240 --> 00:14:20.056
Lucia. are you okay?

98
00:14:20.080 --> 00:14:22.560
Slut!

99
00:14:23.400 --> 00:14:26.400
The fuck you doing? Hitting my face?

100
00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:31.416
You wanna save them?

101
00:14:31.440 --> 00:14:33.656
You wanna save them?

102
00:14:33.680 --> 00:14:35.296
I'll slit your throat!

103
00:14:35.320 --> 00:14:36.936
I'm going to kill you!

104
00:14:36.960 --> 00:14:40.080
Stop the fucking brokers.

105
00:14:41.160 --> 00:14:43.480
Bye. Stefano.

106
00:14:43.920 --> 00:14:45.856
Wait!

107
00:14:45.880 --> 00:14:47.656
What was that?

108
00:14:47.680 --> 00:14:51.216
- We can stop the brokers.
- Yeah? How?

109
00:14:51.240 --> 00:14:55.160
- We can stop them.
- How? Tell me.

110
00:14:56.880 --> 00:14:58.896
- I know where the cargo is.
- Really?

111
00:14:58.920 --> 00:15:00.896
I know where the cargo is!

112
00:15:00.920 --> 00:15:04.056
My grandfather told me
how to trace it.

113
00:15:04.080 --> 00:15:06.640
Open the door. Gianpietro.

114
00:15:49.840 --> 00:15:53.640
I didn't think my sons
would betray Don Minu.

115
00:15:54.160 --> 00:15:57.480
At least let my son go.

116
00:16:01.600 --> 00:16:04.096
My sons were wrong.

117
00:16:04.120 --> 00:16:06.936
but they're my blood.

118
00:16:06.960 --> 00:16:09.640
I can't abandon them.

119
00:16:10.600 --> 00:16:13.880
They'll slit your throats. one by one.

120
00:16:16.200 --> 00:16:20.360
Don Minu will make
the Bellantone family disappear.

121
00:16:49.760 --> 00:16:53.320
- Good to see you. Stefano.
- Thanks. let's go.

122
00:16:53.360 --> 00:16:57.736
- Pleased to see you.
- Pleasure's all mine.

123
00:16:57.760 --> 00:16:59.816
Who's he?

124
00:16:59.840 --> 00:17:01.816
He's with me.

125
00:17:01.840 --> 00:17:03.656
Alright.

126
00:17:03.680 --> 00:17:06.840
- Get in the car.
- Thanks.

127
00:17:20.720 --> 00:17:22.536
How are things here?

128
00:17:22.560 --> 00:17:25.056
They're good.

129
00:17:25.080 --> 00:17:29.320
What's new up there?
How's Don Minu?

130
00:17:30.120 --> 00:17:32.176
He's good.

131
00:17:32.200 --> 00:17:36.480
I'm glad. Your wife and son?

132
00:17:39.360 --> 00:17:42.720
The boy's six now.

133
00:17:43.680 --> 00:17:47.656
Have you found the two brokers
who've got the shipment?

134
00:17:47.680 --> 00:17:50.096
We'll figure it out.
I've already spoken to a friend.

135
00:17:50.120 --> 00:17:53.640
- So. we know how?
- Of course.

136
00:17:59.280 --> 00:18:03.176
There's a woman. Amina.
she's the fixer's daughter.

137
00:18:03.200 --> 00:18:07.056
She works with him.
they've got an office down at the port.

138
00:18:07.080 --> 00:18:10.816
- How much longer?
- A few minutes. we're nearly there.

139
00:18:10.840 --> 00:18:16.120
Yasser. the father.
is the Lynwoods' fixer in Casablanca.

140
00:18:25.960 --> 00:18:29.400
In my heart. I'm praying for you.

141
00:18:35.960 --> 00:18:38.400
Here.

142
00:18:45.280 --> 00:18:47.480
Amina?

143
00:18:47.640 --> 00:18:49.880
Yes?

144
00:18:50.080 --> 00:18:53.040
Can I help you?

145
00:19:42.160 --> 00:19:44.696
I'm giving you what you want.

146
00:19:44.720 --> 00:19:47.256
I'm giving you what you want.

147
00:19:47.280 --> 00:19:48.936
I don't get it.

148
00:19:48.960 --> 00:19:51.456
Now give me your word
of honour in front of him

149
00:19:51.480 --> 00:19:55.040
that you'll free Lucia and my son.

150
00:20:01.120 --> 00:20:03.136
Word of honour.

151
00:20:03.160 --> 00:20:06.080
Are we clear?

152
00:20:06.720 --> 00:20:09.160
Yes.

153
00:31:00.360 --> 00:31:03.600
- Hi. Dad.
- Hi. darling.

154
00:31:07.800 --> 00:31:10.216
Later go fix everything at the port.

155
00:31:10.240 --> 00:31:14.320
I have an appointment at Customs.

156
00:40:42.840 --> 00:40:46.040
What are you doing here in the street?

157
00:44:25.320 --> 00:44:29.880
Where are you?
Check nobody is following you.

158
00:44:38.680 --> 00:44:42.160
Thanks. bye.

159
00:46:17.600 --> 00:46:20.400
Where is it?

160
00:46:21.800 --> 00:46:24.840
Ask him where it is.

161
00:46:29.440 --> 00:46:32.016
- What did he say?
- Keep going.

162
00:46:32.040 --> 00:46:34.960
Keep going straight.

163
00:46:35.840 --> 00:46:38.800
And let's keep going.

164
00:47:24.480 --> 00:47:25.656
Get that?

165
00:47:25.680 --> 00:47:27.856
Yeah. but left. where?

166
00:47:27.880 --> 00:47:30.120
He'll tell us.

167
00:47:41.200 --> 00:47:44.920
Time two minutes. please.

168
00:48:51.520 --> 00:48:53.496
Hello.

169
00:48:53.520 --> 00:48:56.240
Can I help you?

170
00:49:29.800 --> 00:49:32.320
Open it.

171
00:49:34.280 --> 00:49:36.760
Come on!

172
00:50:20.000 --> 00:50:22.176
Open it.

173
00:50:22.200 --> 00:50:24.520
Move!

174
00:50:49.280 --> 00:50:51.800
Move.

175
00:51:25.400 --> 00:51:27.880
What did he say?

176
00:51:42.560 --> 00:51:46.000
Now what did he say?

177
00:51:46.120 --> 00:51:49.600
I'm talking to you!

178
00:51:55.240 --> 00:51:58.376
- He says the shipment's left.
- It's left?

179
00:51:58.400 --> 00:52:00.976
And you knew it. Stefano.

180
00:52:01.000 --> 00:52:03.656
- You think I knew?
- You knew.

181
00:52:03.680 --> 00:52:06.320
Piece of shit!

182
00:52:09.520 --> 00:52:10.816
Piece of shit!

183
00:52:10.840 --> 00:52:14.560
You made me run around
like a fucking idiot.

184
00:52:42.880 --> 00:52:45.936
Stop! Stop!

185
00:52:45.960 --> 00:52:48.936
Stefano. come here.

186
00:52:48.960 --> 00:52:52.240
Come here.

187
00:52:53.680 --> 00:52:56.256
Calm down. Stefano.

188
00:52:56.280 --> 00:52:57.736
Calm down.

189
00:52:57.760 --> 00:52:59.896
Let's go.

190
00:52:59.920 --> 00:53:02.336
Now you gotta do something.

191
00:53:02.360 --> 00:53:06.320
Find your grandfather and kill him.

192
00:53:07.400 --> 00:53:10.400
For Lucia and Domenico.

193
00:53:15.400 --> 00:53:18.400
Let's go. guys.

194
00:53:28.240 --> 00:53:30.440
Let's go!

195
00:53:30.680 --> 00:53:33.600
Stefano. come on.

196
00:53:35.920 --> 00:53:38.296
Get in the car. let's go!

197
00:53:38.320 --> 00:53:40.816
Let's get out of this shithole.

198
00:53:40.840 --> 00:53:44.840
We're going home.
